title: Low-flying A380 causes near panic in Dubai
text:
Low-flying A380 causes near panic in Dubai   
Oct 12, 2015 eTN   
DUBAI, United Arab Emirates - An Emirates A380 has been spotted flying low across parts of Dubai, including Dubai Marina, The Palm Jumeirah and the Arabian Sea. 
But after a wave of near panic on social media, Emirates said that there is nothing to fear: airline has confirmed it was conducting air to air filming and a test flight of the double decker jumbo. 
Twitter users were quick to suggest all was not well, with some even suggesting that a fighter jet was seen flying close to the A380. This could not be confirmed, but if air to air filming was taking place, then itâ€™s quite likely one plane was filming the other.
